{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/warts-verrucae/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"99c23bdf-3dca-5be9-900a-20a76728fcbf","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 691846e9-2c4b-41f3-beb8-f4690adc3d90 --><h2>How should I diagnose warts and verrucae?</h2><!-- end field 691846e9-2c4b-41f3-beb8-f4690adc3d90 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 55601f48-52cd-4961-9ea6-79858f027ad5 --><!-- begin field 0df98804-9550-4c1c-a77d-b78fee9a7531 --><ul><li><strong>Warts are diagnosed from their typical appearance. </strong><ul><li><strong>Common warts: </strong>firm, raised papules with a rough surface that resembles a cauliflower (common on knuckles, knees, and fingers) — usually asymptomatic but may be tender.<ul><li><strong>Periungual warts</strong> are common warts around the nails that can be painful and disturb nail growth — nail biting is a risk factor.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Plane warts</strong>: usually round, flat-topped, and skin coloured or greyish yellow (common on the backs of hands).</li><li><strong>Filiform warts: </strong>finger-like appearance and may have a stalk (more common on the face and neck).</li><li><strong>Palmar and plantar warts: </strong>grow on the palms and the soles of the feet (verrucae). They often have central dark dots (thrombosed capillaries) and may be painful.</li><li><strong>Mosaic warts </strong>occur when palmar or plantar warts coalesce into larger plaques on the hands and feet.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Diagnosis is usually clinical and in most people further investigations are not required.</strong><ul><li>If there is diagnostic doubt, light paring of a wart will reveal tiny black dots on the surface (thrombosed capillaries) but be aware that bleeding may lead to warts spreading<strong>.</strong></li><li>If lesions are atypical <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/warts-verrucae/management/management/#referral\">referral</a> for specialist assessment should be arranged.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 0df98804-9550-4c1c-a77d-b78fee9a7531 --><!-- end item 55601f48-52cd-4961-9ea6-79858f027ad5 -->","topic":{"id":"41c94fc3-84c7-5d23-b0c1-b340dde561cf","topicId":"428bb097-7256-4343-b880-fb429b718d6d","topicName":"Warts and verrucae","slug":"warts-verrucae","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2020","chapters":[{"id":"1b91075b-35e9-580a-a349-b2aecac3712b","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"0ad476a8-9abf-5e68-8b94-60889f87963c","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"0c70c378-3d0c-573b-829d-ad3fe85ba7be","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"8117e71e-2ea4-540c-97dc-6f57d76c3eb9","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"20fb58f7-f730-5521-8a3e-e928324e4652","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"65d1b9d9-b162-5e9b-bfb9-98d935069c7f","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"6acab5c8-0505-5af9-8070-472e0850b28c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"f5c53f23-1d42-550a-ade0-09928c029282","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"4f36f273-a3e3-5263-9d17-cde56dabdabe","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"6134b512-75ff-5330-9138-7c89c3f528f7","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"c1fcf745-8b2c-55ba-853a-44e100100069","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"06ece2e8-1a04-508d-8f13-e45ab5493948","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"50827b1e-9574-5139-8bdd-a5cbcd82a9b8","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"f4d6c184-5397-5bc0-